<br>
First, the spell is relatively rare... without a doubt the rarest spell for Enchanters to get.  That naturally makes it more expensive...<br>
<br>
Second, in all honesty I think the 5% slow in and of itself is worth it.  Marginal benefit becomes more important as our levels increase, and therefore becomes more expensive.<br>
<br>
Finally, there are some that think Shiftless Deeds is not a consistent slow spell to 65%.  Therefore Forlorn Deeds at least gives you a higher minimum slow %.  I never tested it nor do I know if there is any truth to that theory.<br>
<br>
BTW... if you think 8k is bad, a guildmate of mine had to trade almost 100k for his spell about a year ago.<br>
